From 423780f093ccda73da1f87bf2f953384d78681ed Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Micheal Waltz <micheal@ecliptik.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 17:52:11 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 3/9] [DOSKUTSU] cmake: rename DJGPP binary to doskutsu
 (DOSKUTSU.EXE)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Why DOS needs this: the doskutsu project ships its binary as `DOSKUTSU.EXE`
on the target CF card (per CLAUDE.md project naming + locked decision #9 in
PLAN.md). Upstream NXEngine-evo names its CMake target `nx` with
`OUTPUT_NAME nxengine-evo`, producing `nxengine-evo.exe` — not what we
ship. DOS's 8.3 filename limit would force `NXENGIN~1.EXE`, which is uglier
than just emitting the right name from the build.

Approach: scope the rename to DJGPP toolchain detection so non-DOS builds
(Linux / macOS / Windows native, etc.) keep upstream's `nxengine-evo`
binary name. This keeps the patch a strict superset on those platforms —
nothing changes if a user builds upstream on Linux against this fork.

DJGPP / DOS produces `doskutsu.exe`; FAT-write uppercase auto-conversion
turns it into `DOSKUTSU.EXE` on the CF card. The Makefile's
post-build step copies the produced binary to `build/doskutsu.exe` so the
installation path is consistent across host filesystems.

Detection guard matches 0002-cmake-djgpp-target-flags.patch — same
predicate, same rationale (toolchain prefix or system name).

A future patch in slot 0006-0009 may also bump the DPMI minimum stack via
stubedit (`stubedit doskutsu.exe minstack=2048k`); for now that runs as a
post-link Makefile rule outside this patch's scope.
---
 CMakeLists.txt | 9 ++++++++-
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
index 0d0fb27..f9df7d2 100644
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -128,7 +128,14 @@ endif()
 add_executable(nx ${SOURCES})
 
 IF(PLATFORM STREQUAL "pc")
-    set_property(TARGET nx PROPERTY OUTPUT_NAME nxengine-evo)
+    # Binary rename: doskutsu ships as DOSKUTSU.EXE on the target CF card.
+    # DJGPP / DOS 8.3 filenames uppercase the basename automatically at FAT-write
+    # time, so emitting `doskutsu.exe` here produces `DOSKUTSU.EXE` on disk.
+    if(CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME STREQUAL "MSDOS" OR CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER MATCHES "msdosdjgpp")
+        set_property(TARGET nx PROPERTY OUTPUT_NAME doskutsu)
+    else()
+        set_property(TARGET nx PROPERTY OUTPUT_NAME nxengine-evo)
+    endif()
     add_definitions("-std=c++11")
     IF(UNIX_LIKE)
         add_definitions(-DHAVE_UNIX_LIKE)
-- 
